

'''= calendar for publishing and being aware of new events about Open source hardware, digital fabrication, hacking, and all kind of events that could concern the makers community'''

URL = http://makerscalendar.cc

=Description=

'Makers calendar is a simple calendar for publishing and being aware of new events about Open source hardware, digital fabrication, hacking, and all kind of events that could concerned the makers community all around the world.
Publishing an event into the Makers calendar is really easy: you only have to fill the form, in the language you want, and we'll publish it.
To follow the makers calendar news, you can subscribe to the calendar or only to one kind of events subscribing to a single category. You can also follow the makers calendar through twitter.

It's an easy way to be up to date and to publish events from and for the makers community."


=More Information=


If you want to contribute, email us to fred@ultra-lab.net

So, the makers calendar is here http://makerscalendar.cc
and its twitter account is @makerscalendar


